[ctns_make id='ptEqnS1']

    [ctns_front]
Particular Equation
    [/ctns_front]

    [ctns_back style='font-size:90%;max-width:400px']
An equation, e.g.,
$|y=3x+7|$
is called a <strong>particular equation</strong> when all constant values, e.g., $$m=3$$ and $$b=7$$, are specified.
    [/ctns_back]

    [ctns_backspeak]
An equation is called a particular equation when all constant values are specified.
    [/ctns_backspeak]

[/ctns_make]



[ctns_make id='gnEqnS1']

    [ctns_front]
General Equation
    [/ctns_front]

    [ctns_back style='width:80%;font-size:90%;']
An equation, e.g.,
$|y=mx+b|$
is called a <strong>general equation</strong> when all constant values, e.g., $$m$$ and $$b$$, are not specified.
    [/ctns_back]

    [ctns_backspeak]
An equation is called a general equation when all constant values are not specified.
    [/ctns_backspeak]

[/ctns_make]



[ctns_make id='funcDefS1']

    [ctns_front]
Function
    [/ctns_front]

    [ctns_back style='width:70%;font-size:90%;']
A <strong>function</strong> is a mapping $$A \rightarrow B$$ that assigns to each element of the set $$A$$, called the <em>domain</em>, exactly one element of the set $$B,$$ called the <em>range</em>.
    [/ctns_back]

    [ctns_backspeak]
A function is a mapping from set A to set B that assigns to each element of the set A, called the domain, exactly one element of the set B, called the range.
    [/ctns_backspeak]

[/ctns_make]




[ctns_make id='funcRelS1']

    [ctns_front]
Relation
    [/ctns_front]

    [ctns_back style='width:70%;font-size:90%;']
A <strong>relation</strong> is a set of ordered pairs.
    [/ctns_back]

[/ctns_make]




[ctns_make id='funcRanS1']

    [ctns_front]
Range
    [/ctns_front]

    [ctns_back style='width:70%;font-size:90%;']
The <strong>range</strong> of a function is the set of values of the <em>dependent</em> variable corresponding to all values of the independent variable in the domain.
    [/ctns_back]

[/ctns_make]



[ctns_make id='funcDomS1']

    [ctns_front]
Domain
    [/ctns_front]

    [ctns_back style='width:70%;font-size:90%;']
The <strong>domain</strong> of a function is the set of values of the <em>independent</em> variable.
    [/ctns_back]

[/ctns_make]
